WHO   — crond — the running daemon that wakes (classically each minute), reads the tables, and launches whatever is due — the living process behind the schedule
WHAT  — the running daemon that wakes (classically each minute), reads the tables, and launches whatever is due — the living process behind the schedule
WHERE — CRN · The Cron Job — Unix scheduling, ~1975 → today (LOGISMÓS domain)  Framework inputs: cron; crontab; crond; the schedule; the box; the watch  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — It is patience as a program: a thing whose entire life is waiting for the right second and then acting, every minute, until the machine dies.
HOW   — Crystallized from the history & practice of cron.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
